{"id":14881402,"mediaExerciseId":"dd7429fb-e46c-4e5b-ae1b-ad2dc67277cf","exerciseName":"3","chapterName":"13","chapterTitle":"Return, Risk, and The Security Market Line","groupId":612376,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":451,"solutions":[{"id":5994625,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the portfolio's expected return. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/5a7005bbfc4851cc9ba616664a9fa81a/lateximg_large.png","width":985},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/5a7005bbfc4851cc9ba616664a9fa81a/lateximg.png","width":492}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is the net income or loss that an investor predicts on investments given known interest rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/4912f54cb2730c9108f6c1c9b210ea03/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/4912f54cb2730c9108f6c1c9b210ea03/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's first identify the given amounts in the problem: \n\n\n| | Amount$\\hspace{5pt}$| \n|:--|--:| \n|Stock X: ||\n|Probability return | 35% | \n|Expected return |9%|\n|Stock Y: ||\n|Probability return | 20%| \n|Expected return |15%|\n|Stock Z: ||\n|Probability return | 45%| \n|Expected return |12%|","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The **expected return** is computed as follows: \n\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&=\\sum_{\\text{}}{\\text{}_{R}} {\\text{PR $\\times$ R}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere: \n\nPR = Probability return \\\nR = Return","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":220,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/75deb0d751442cd61cce66b41b94e519/lateximg_large.png","width":702},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/75deb0d751442cd61cce66b41b94e519/lateximg.png","width":351}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let us insert the provided data to the formula from step 4. As an illustration, here's what it looks like: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&= {\\text{(35\\% $\\times$ 9\\%) + (20\\% $\\times$ 15\\%) + (45\\% $\\times$ 12\\%)}}\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/f75074e8168c7da2f3db3f14113594ed/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":73,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/f75074e8168c7da2f3db3f14113594ed/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let us compute the portfolios's expected return. This is computed as follows: \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Expected return}&= {\\text{(35\\% $\\times$ 9\\%) + (20\\% $\\times$ 15\\%) + (45\\% $\\times$ 12\\%)}}\\\\\n&={\\text{3.15\\% + 3\\% + 5.4\\%}}\\\\\n&={\\textbf{11.55\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":221,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/8e04dac262d23db83fb60a13ce36468b/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":112,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/ffb3010487351c81b261bea4903b9766/8e04dac262d23db83fb60a13ce36468b/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"**To conclude, the portfolio's expected return is 11.55%.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"4d43da30-e50c-41a0-b07c-31614380e8bd","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881403,"exerciseName":"4","page":451,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ae2fcf2e-0021-4200-af02-c72790e5f4cf","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-4-ae2fcf2e-0021-4200-af02-c72790e5f4cf"},{"id":14881404,"exerciseName":"5","page":452,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"4c95f9d5-a579-4285-9d1a-1da46ca05c8e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-13-questions-and-problems-5-4c95f9d5-a579-4285-9d1a-1da46ca05c8e"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881401,"exerciseName":"2","page":451,"hasSolut